x4freetext: Update of 1987 and 1992 evaluation
I.Dillmann+, KADoNiS v0.3

x4codes.shortRef: Jour: Atomic Data and Nuclear Data Tables, Vol.36, p.411 (1987)

x4freetext: Z.Y.Bao+, previous compilation
Evaluation:
- The experimental results for nuclei between H and Bi
were critically surveyed, renormalized to selected
standard cross sections.
- Cross sections calculated by statistical model NON-
SMOKER were adopted in those cases where
experimental information is still missing (majority
of radioactive nuclei defining the s-process
branching).
KADoNiS v0.3 was released in 28 August 2009.

x4code.headerHelp: Error in value of quantity, defined under ERR-ANALYS

x4freetext: Essentially evaluated from the systematic
errors quoted for the experimental data.
Since most publications were not detailed enough with
respect to error estimates, no critical judgment on
these was attempted.
Nevertheless, these error estimates appeared fairly
realistic in general.
On
On. REFERENCE revised, REL-REF deleted
On. Major revision in 344-345.
